Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 8.1",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Atomic emission spectra of alkali and alkaline-earth atoms. B\[EAcute]laB\
\[EAcute]la, Wikimedia, 2015, CC-BY-SA 4.0, \
https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Alkali_and_alkaline_earth_metals_\
emission_spectrum.png"
}], "Affiliation",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809435027311596*^9, 3.8094350763900714`*^9}, {
  3.80943583474421*^9, 3.8094358359299717`*^9}, {3.8094472165104203`*^9, 
  3.809447281165168*^9}, {3.810054221304062*^9, 3.8100542409148703`*^9}, {
  3.8101125924447937`*^9, 3.8101126426025887`*^9}, {3.8101127071459217`*^9, 
  3.810112714050138*^9}, {3.810115126505663*^9, 3.810115154403865*^9}, {
  3.8101152097595587`*^9, 3.8101152368678613`*^9}, {3.8104844563968916`*^9, 
  3.8104844576598825`*^9}, {3.810716456400798*^9, 3.8107166740108333`*^9}, {
  3.810716839152422*^9, 3.8107168476612215`*^9}, {3.8107171062759004`*^9, 
  3.8107171338184347`*^9}, {3.8107173818819304`*^9, 3.81071741604937*^9}, {
  3.8127335786160326`*^9, 3.8127335799592395`*^9}, {3.812733619587339*^9, 
  3.812733624639125*^9}, {3.918380585959895*^9, 
  3.9183806844990883`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c3add466-8eff-4f63-bb57-\
7aa7d6953608"],

Cell["\<\
As a more direct example of the utility of atomic emission spectra, consider \
the spectrum shown in Figure 8.2, which shows emission spectra collected by \
the NASA Mars Curiosity Rover. These spectra were collected following laser \
ablation of a rock surface, which provided the necessary energy input to \
excite the electrons and thus initiate emission of light. Using these \
results, NASA scientists were able to assess the composition of rocks on the \
surface of Mars.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.918380716199383*^9, 3.91838079707953*^9}, {
  3.9183808786288004`*^9, 
  3.918380956551756*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a6d76969-5fd1-49de-8e68-\
451070e4fa6d"],

