  3.9184054060618114`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dd459783-f60b-48e1-8497-\
34454d5b3db2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In addition, now we also have to account for spin, which means we are \
adding two vectors with unspecified ",
 StyleBox["x",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["y",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " components. The addition of spin and orbital angular momentum vectors is \
depicted in Figure 8.5 for a generic case of spin and angular momentum \
vectors adding to give the total angular momentum (typically denoted as ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ")."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8127336405312095`*^9, 3.812733702900323*^9}, {
  3.812733762035598*^9, 3.81273380861458*^9}, {3.8127338971455736`*^9, 
  3.8127339211693344`*^9}, {3.9184033639154377`*^9, 3.9184033648118577`*^9}, {
  3.9184054148553486`*^9, 
  3.9184054149939733`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cc56ed65-5554-49a2-85d8-\
3c8170305abb"],

