DAUFheMhc0wYWblAOYaCgsKxkDlmHlCOoaCgcDwox1BQUDgTlGMoKCicCcox
FBQUzgTlGAoKCmeCcgwFBYUzQTmGgoLCmaAcQ0FB4UxQjqGgoHAmKMdQUFA4
E5RjKCgonAnKMRQUFM6EkmPyyWoo3VZXzuFQUFBUMyg5poCsRtJtyjEUFBSO
AOUYCgoKZ0LmmNlAOYaCgsLxkDlmGlCOoaCgcDwox1BQUDgTlGMoKCicCcox
FBQUzgTlGAoKCmeCcgwFBYUzQTmGgoLCmaAcQ0FB4UzIHBNCVh5QjqGgoHAs
lHm+PFkPSLcpx1BQUDgCMpf0J+tLsmpLt2lvB4pKx/8Bxhaz6g==
    "], {{0, 300.}, {281., 0}}, {0, 255},
    ColorFunction->RGBColor],
   BoxForm`ImageTag["Byte", ColorSpace -> "RGB", Interleaving -> True],
   Selectable->False],
  DefaultBaseStyle->"ImageGraphics",
  ImageSizeRaw->{281., 300.},
  PlotRange->{{0, 281.}, {0, 300.}}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.810716348934929*^9, 3.8127336040473113`*^9, 
  3.8127338807548313`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[23]=",ExpressionUUID->"9764c851-7730-4ded-a79a-21ab398233ad"]
}, {2}]],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 8.5",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Depiction of the addition of orbital angular momentum vector ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "and spin angular momentum vector ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " to give the total angular momentum vector ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "."
}], "Affiliation",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809435027311596*^9, 3.8094350763900714`*^9}, {
  3.80943583474421*^9, 3.8094358359299717`*^9}, {3.8094472165104203`*^9, 
  3.809447281165168*^9}, {3.810054221304062*^9, 3.8100542409148703`*^9}, {
  3.8101125924447937`*^9, 3.8101126426025887`*^9}, {3.8101127071459217`*^9, 
  3.810112714050138*^9}, {3.810115126505663*^9, 3.810115154403865*^9}, {
  3.8101152097595587`*^9, 3.8101152368678613`*^9}, {3.8104844563968916`*^9, 
  3.8104844576598825`*^9}, {3.810716456400798*^9, 3.8107166740108333`*^9}, {
  3.810716839152422*^9, 3.8107168476612215`*^9}, {3.8107171062759004`*^9, 
  3.8107171338184347`*^9}, {3.8107173818819304`*^9, 3.81071741604937*^9}, {
  3.8127335786160326`*^9, 3.8127335799592395`*^9}, {3.812733619587339*^9, 
  3.812733624639125*^9}, {3.812733931147242*^9, 3.81273398308552*^9}, {
  3.9184033758963537`*^9, 3.9184033766106915`*^9}, {3.918405417998373*^9, 
  3.918405418171404*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3223138d-c1cf-4077-960d-\
c3334cb99f00"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The main method that we use to avoid such complexity is to restrict \
ourselves to addition of the ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " component of both spin and orbital angular momentum, which is simply \
additive and therefore much easier to work with. Using this approach, we can \
take a sum over the spin and orbital angular momentum for each electron in a \
multielectron atom and thereby attain the z-component of the angular momentum \
for the multielectron atom."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812733996008459*^9, 3.8127341187714834`*^9}, {
  3.918403476001502*^9, 
  3.9184034763376007`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"eeb746dd-241a-45f1-8f65-\
b25b26b2a033"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Term Symbols as a Descriptor of Electron Configuration", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128100882278576`*^9, 3.812810100703714*^9}, {
  3.8128105497772408`*^9, 
  3.8128105513972025`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d3cfe4bf-a489-4fe8-a83c-\
d6c21462b20b"],

Cell["\<\
Quantifying the spin, orbital, and total angular momentum of an atom provides \
a unique description of the electron configuration. We usually write down \
these values in a specific format, which we know as a term symbol.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128101060123453`*^9, 3.812810263403099*^9}, {
  3.91840433048407*^9, 
  3.918404333539178*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5a971777-a150-4101-991a-\
fe6bb40435a0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s further consider how an electron configuration alone \
does not fully specify the state of an atom. For example, the ground-state \
electron configuration of carbon may be written as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"1", 
    SuperscriptBox["s", "2"], "2", 
    SuperscriptBox["s", "2"], "2", 
    SuperscriptBox["p", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "14b62638-7e26-4b2b-86c1-9a18985e276f"],
 ". However, this description does not tell us which ",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " orbitals are occupied and what the spin states of the two ",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " electrons are. When we employ term symbols, we specify the electron \
configuration in greater detail."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128102685162177`*^9, 3.8128103897719994`*^9}, {
  3.8128105690943546`*^9, 3.8128106047314253`*^9}, {3.9184043606538415`*^9, 
  3.918404403697343*^9}, {3.937052346648184*^9, 
  3.9370523474722004`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a88a23a8-10b6-4128-af88-\
71fb8a97093f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To write the term symbol, there are three pieces of information we need to \
know: the total orbital angular momentum ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", the total spin angular momentum ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", and the total angular momentum ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "(which is given by ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "+ ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "). The term symbol is then constructed as"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128104283070498`*^9, 3.8128105080963526`*^9}, {
  3.812810608576682*^9, 
  3.812810620697047*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b2446cd5-e79c-40dc-8451-\
5a5db5d8b81a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox["", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"2", 
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "+", "1"}]], 
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["L",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["J",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128106336360607`*^9, 
  3.8128106849647636`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"944e582d-6a9d-46f3-9512-\
6527fa4741cb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where we are using the magnitude of  ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ",  ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", and ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", and ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". When writing the magnitude of the total orbital angular momentum ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", we use a letter code,"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128106997541003`*^9, 3.8128107497079477`*^9}, {
  3.8128107842743998`*^9, 
  3.8128108478931165`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cf845e88-c475-44e4-8826-\
92765703aa2f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
    {
     StyleBox["L",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", "0", "1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "..."},
    {" ", " ", 
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["P",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["D",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["F",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["G",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["H",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "..."}
   }], "\[NoBreak]"}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128108612387547`*^9, 3.8128108663038797`*^9}, {
  3.8128108967855253`*^9, 3.812810931478409*^9}, {3.8128110701849627`*^9, 
  3.8128111062398863`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9241df6a-dc69-47c9-a999-\
de3d88956516"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "which you may recognize as analogous to that used for the angular momentum \
of hydrogen orbitals (",
 StyleBox["s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["d",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ...). The difference in this case is that we are referring to the angular \
momentum of all of the electrons, not just a single electron in an orbital."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128111120979385`*^9, 3.812811167791029*^9}, {
  3.9184044409971733`*^9, 
  3.918404453070178*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"30c4a072-ce18-436e-9163-\
6756a019efdd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Remember that we said we obtain ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " by adding up the vectors of orbital angular momentum and spin angular \
momentum, respectively. In equation form, we would write"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128116197222757`*^9, 3.8128117295824385`*^9}, {
  3.812811886695732*^9, 
  3.812811898152213*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"03565743-2e95-4c80-8ba6-\
221dac8d2d19"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["L",
   FontWeight->"Bold",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["l",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 
  3.812811805160163*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5d9acf8d-d132-4d87-b73a-\
8f96d8e7c9db"],

Cell["and", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812811813511904*^9, 
  3.812811815610421*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"da302101-0ca7-4d1c-8dd2-\
d77eb3ec8551"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["S",
   FontWeight->"Bold",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["s",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.8128118382979555`*^9}, {
  3.812811900904417*^9, 
  3.812811908204573*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"acb3a250-e9ed-4549-9baf-\
1223c6f567f5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 StyleBox["i",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " represents an iterator over  each electron. As mentioned in the previous \
section, adding up the vectors ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["l",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["i",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"34f0f7d1-709e-4cd4-b3c5-364503f0e3da"],
 " or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["s",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["i",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.8128118382979555`*^9}, {
   3.812811900904417*^9, 3.812811908204573*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "878cc35c-a68b-4e5b-b28c-c725908dd495"],
 " is not straightforward, so we instead add their corresponding ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " components ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["l",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"39c9737e-155f-49bc-988c-cfd6b03ee127"],
 " or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["s",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"245c1ea4-4bcc-4782-9f8a-8f25017ad44c"],
 ". Because the ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " components are always along the ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " axis, we can simply add them as scalars and don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t have to \
worry about what direction they are pointing. We then define the total ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " component of ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " as"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128118415889997`*^9, 3.8128118479138107`*^9}, {
   3.812811911862792*^9, 3.8128121078989983`*^9}, {3.812812160646432*^9, 
   3.8128121988535695`*^9}, {3.81281268508466*^9, 3.812812689139732*^9}, {
   3.9184044680183125`*^9, 3.918404498791123*^9}, 
   3.937053731204054*^9},ExpressionUUID->"4995406f-6f83-4b4b-8f83-\
2116949ed8b2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["L",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["m",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["li",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "              ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", 
       StyleBox["L",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"-", 
        StyleBox["L",
         FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "+", "1"}], ",", "...", ",", "0", ",", "...",
       ",", 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["L",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "-", "1"}], ",", 
      StyleBox["L",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
     StyleBox[")",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
  3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
  3.8128123854295173`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8dac1745-8d65-4b3d-a8d5-\
17c7333256d3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "and the total ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " component of ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " as"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812812231756082*^9, 
  3.8128122455063386`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7402181e-a536-4269-b2e9-\
1958ec32b449"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["m",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["si",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "              ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", 
       StyleBox["S",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"-", 
        StyleBox["S",
         FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "+", "1"}], ",", "...", ",", "0", ",", "...",
       ",", 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["S",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "-", "1"}], ",", 
      StyleBox["S",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
     StyleBox[")",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
  3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.81281225334006*^9}, {3.812812390709155*^9, 
  3.8128124123886204`*^9}, {3.812812973199164*^9, 
  3.812812973843424*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"676a59b5-778f-4f29-aa2b-\
db3313f23999"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Note the similarity between the allowed values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["L",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
   3.8128123854295173`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "866c3de0-4a6c-456e-992d-de7e47652a60"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.81281225334006*^9}, {3.812812390709155*^9, 
   3.8128124123886204`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "230e79bc-9fac-45ba-9571-5ac67bc948a8"],
 " and the allowed values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["l",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
   3.8128123854295173`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "a0fafb6a-eb0e-4d6a-8dec-927829f53dcb"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["s",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.81281225334006*^9}, {3.812812390709155*^9, 
   3.8128124123886204`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "38ff366e-d3e7-4a3a-8ac9-adf384faedfc"],
 ". Also, note that when we write"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128124207258234`*^9, 3.812812469663701*^9}, {
  3.8129046650275106`*^9, 
  3.812904665639507*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f80a7cf4-b303-4873-99ac-\
c99b326ff80d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"2", 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "+", "1"}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128106336360607`*^9, 3.8128106849647636`*^9}, {
  3.812811228054324*^9, 
  3.8128112309425654`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0b65dcf1-e4d6-4879-8884-\
16b858e19ce2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "in our term symbol, we are actually writing the number of possible values \
of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.81281225334006*^9}, {3.812812390709155*^9, 
   3.8128124123886204`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "1d827eb1-5cfe-461f-b26c-bf497e91e573"],
 " for a given value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["S",
   FontWeight->"Plain",
   FontSlant->"Italic"]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.81281225334006*^9}, {3.812812390709155*^9, 
   3.8128124123886204`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "d35d2e68-749c-4a49-aaf0-14be7b3a7096"],
 ". This value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["2",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "+", "1"}],
   FontWeight->"Plain"]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.81281225334006*^9}, {3.812812390709155*^9, 
   3.8128124123886204`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "eb3c9756-50aa-45dd-92c0-d1dd671682fe"],
 " is known as the spin multiplicity."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812812472839081*^9, 
  3.8128125557655478`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9b35dab3-2f70-4bb6-8139-\
4b90be44d2e2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Finally, remember that we also are interested in the total angular momentum \
",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". As with  ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", the ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " component of ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is much easier to work with. Therefore, we label the ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " component of ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["J",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
   3.8128123854295173`*^9}, {3.812812734843032*^9, 3.812812738001706*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"85d3ab7b-82b4-4172-9e89-c98c8a109618"],
 ", which we define as"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128126111921864`*^9, 3.812812665095096*^9}, {
  3.8128126989088182`*^9, 
  3.8128127724394474`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fd1aa4f0-cf03-4386-81b3-\
62a2a38b832a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["J",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["M",
     FontWeight->"Plain",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["L",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontWeight->"Plain",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "            ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", 
       StyleBox["J",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"-", 
        StyleBox["J",
         FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "+", "1"}], ",", "...", ",", "0", ",", "...",
       ",", 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["J",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "-", "1"}], ",", 
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
     StyleBox[")",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
   3.8128123854295173`*^9}, {3.812812734843032*^9, 3.812812738001706*^9}, {
   3.812812777924115*^9, 3.812812784141674*^9}, {3.8128129529930706`*^9, 
   3.8128130907006335`*^9}, 3.812813186181301*^9, {3.812817470559614*^9, 
   3.8128174884674053`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dcd92a50-95fd-42c0-abec-\
0d9e2c75bad5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Find the Term Symbol of an Atom", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814066047477*^9, 
  3.8128140767197485`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"87fde28a-863f-4319-844d-\
6bf55dc0bc1b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To see how we assign term symbols, let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s first take the \
simple case of an ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["ns",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "13f9d499-e1f1-47ee-a808-c06e30232226"],
 " electron configuration, that is, any ",
 StyleBox["s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " orbital containing two electrons. First, we need to identify the possible \
values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["li",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
   3.8128123854295173`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "a256be19-4516-4a09-999b-e169e0e044e3"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["si",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.81281225334006*^9}, {3.812812390709155*^9, 
   3.8128124123886204`*^9}, {3.812812973199164*^9, 3.812812973843424*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"42a341ae-8f03-423b-91a9-72777354f82f"],
 ", which are "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814080149768*^9, 3.812814081068671*^9}, {
  3.8128141323576593`*^9, 3.8128142892427683`*^9}, {3.8128145011791973`*^9, 
  3.812814508109831*^9}, {3.81281454127048*^9, 3.812814551968996*^9}, {
  3.8128149426704373`*^9, 
  3.812814950888769*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0f3d33b4-3527-4e72-83c2-\
1e8df56edbf1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["si",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   FractionBox["1", "2"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 
  3.8128146034871693`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d64e36b2-1b0d-4dd4-b75d-\
4a1d3a8764f7"],

Cell["and", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814609148638*^9, 
  3.812814609369656*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dc4e8b32-8602-4966-8edb-\
6abebcc25d7a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["li",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", "0"}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 
  3.812814624563648*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"053898bb-c0c6-451d-81ba-\
4a8b7cf8415f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Remember that the two electrons must be in different spin states (although \
we have to write the wavefunction as a linear combination of these mixed spin \
states). So, for this relatively simple case, we see that the only possible \
values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["M", "S"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f77e397a-7501-4296-9c9f-5c75b9187a8e"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["M", "L"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0423b87d-789f-4d6e-8d20-e2346e305f00"],
 " are"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814628125397*^9, 3.812814779276473*^9}, {
  3.81281481173343*^9, 
  3.8128148674517655`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2219903c-0f44-4850-b690-\
d32d148f5cfa"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["M",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["S",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", "0"}], ",", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["M",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["L",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", "0"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 3.8128146034871693`*^9}, {
  3.8128148840894175`*^9, 
  3.8128148974362593`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"bed3297b-2fd0-4e62-8221-\
3c3f04f99508"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Given the relationship between ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["L",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
   3.8128123854295173`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "df4215bd-ca17-4e96-b900-080a6d24d4b6"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and between ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
   3.8128123854295173`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "91ad653f-5ced-48f3-a953-cfbf920e07ce"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", we can also conclude that ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are zero. In addition, because ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["M", "S"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8ed49b0c-3579-433e-9214-59fa49e19cc0"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["M", "L"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2236f465-12c4-4ca2-94a1-f4b51a5e845d"],
 " are both zero, we can conclude that"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128149620252085`*^9, 3.812814995654562*^9}, {
  3.812815062390888*^9, 3.812815123778686*^9}, {3.9184045935841923`*^9, 
  3.9184046078315306`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f1da9e02-d6d4-4be3-bf60-\
f134c3d07397"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["J",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontWeight->"Plain",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["L",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontWeight->"Plain",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}], "=", "0", 
   "            "}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
   3.8128123854295173`*^9}, {3.812812734843032*^9, 3.812812738001706*^9}, {
   3.812812777924115*^9, 3.812812784141674*^9}, {3.8128129529930706`*^9, 
   3.8128130907006335`*^9}, 3.812813186181301*^9, {3.812814998961049*^9, 
   3.8128149993964257`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d236bd80-a550-414f-9a2a-\
bfc01b55bbda"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If the ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " component of ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is zero, then ",
 StyleBox["J ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "is also zero. So the term symbol for this configuration is"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128150432800074`*^9, 3.812815078883189*^9}, {
  3.8128151275852118`*^9, 
  3.8128151948953776`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ba70eb8f-3521-4198-8fbb-\
c7eae35831f1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"2", 
      StyleBox["S",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "+", "1"}]], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["L",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["J",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]]}], 
  SuperscriptBox["=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"2", 
     RowBox[{"(", "0", ")"}]}], "+", "1"}]], 
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["0", "0"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["", "1"], 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "0"]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128152039945197`*^9, 
  3.812815256576949*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"59436a81-f7a0-40ab-9bcb-\
9590074c774f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "which we would say as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]singlet ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " zero\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]. It turns out that ",
 StyleBox["for any closed subshell",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["ns",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], ",", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["np",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "6"], ",", " ", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["nd",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "10"], " ", ",", " ", "..."}], ")"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"10607a22-d9cf-472c-b3c4-e75a59b34a0a"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["the term symbol will always be ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["", "1"], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["S",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "0"]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128152039945197`*^9, 3.812815256576949*^9}},
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"dc829548-4f72-43ce-8856-0433572262b9"],
 ", with values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", "0"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["L",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", "0"}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 3.8128146034871693`*^9}, {
   3.8128148840894175`*^9, 3.8128148974362593`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "baeb6778-ab99-4f15-afe0-5bd7624302c3"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["M",
     FontWeight->"Plain",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["J",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   StyleBox["=",
    FontWeight->"Plain"], "0"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
    3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
    3.8128123854295173`*^9}, {3.812812734843032*^9, 3.812812738001706*^9}, {
    3.812812777924115*^9, 3.812812784141674*^9}, {3.8128129529930706`*^9, 
    3.8128130907006335`*^9}, 3.812813186181301*^9, {3.812814998961049*^9, 
    3.8128149993964257`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "e2643ff8-c6c5-46cf-acb1-765fd7842af5"],
 ". That\[CloseCurlyQuote]s because there will always be an ",
 StyleBox["l",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "l"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "29f6d3f5-b6e9-403a-a644-5304218fe2c8"],
 ", or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "s"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a7a4add4-434d-4875-bb2c-bb368b977673"],
 " state that cancels out with the other, yielding a value of zero. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128152683919053`*^9, 
  3.81281549922764*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c0988086-ea82-4a3e-ad55-\
ea1aa461aacf"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "As closed subshells don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t contribute to the total angular \
momentum, ",
 StyleBox["we only need to concern ourselves with the open shells, usually \
just the valence electrons, to find the term symbol of an atom.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.812815501451036*^9, {3.812815654762288*^9, 3.8128156636553965`*^9}, {
   3.9184046374836082`*^9, 
   3.9184046377324657`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"93b4851b-354e-4669-8b6f-\
0bb44a21a95a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s return now to the example of a ground-state carbon \
atom, which has an electron configuration of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"1", 
    SuperscriptBox["s", "2"], "2", 
    SuperscriptBox["s", "2"], "2", 
    SuperscriptBox["p", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9706427d-3fab-43b6-abc6-2c6c6df790b1"],
 ". We just saw that we can ignore the closed subshells, so we are only \
concerned with the contributions from the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"2", 
    SuperscriptBox["p", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2857b475-5488-477b-a049-5a79a0487f8a"],
 " electrons. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128155950595136`*^9, 
  3.812815782883202*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0aed7a70-b8b5-4edc-86cb-\
9e26b721ec9d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "First, we want to again examine the possible values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["li",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
   3.8128123854295173`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "7b0781aa-14c0-4a6c-b7b6-af22283c19bd"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["si",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
   3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.81281225334006*^9}, {3.812812390709155*^9, 
   3.8128124123886204`*^9}, {3.812812973199164*^9, 3.812812973843424*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"49befe59-99cd-4160-86e4-4d638abd211e"],
 ","
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128157891981277`*^9, 
  3.8128158121149035`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f91aa72a-1b00-4f41-b8da-\
59742fdab60c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["si",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   FractionBox["1", "2"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 
  3.8128146034871693`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"87e5a2ad-7db5-4dec-85d9-\
f0bed3b9ce6c"],

Cell["and", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814609148638*^9, 
  3.812814609369656*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c1836ab5-e0b2-4af4-bdbb-\
3c290cb1ba7c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["m",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["li",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
   RowBox[{"-", "1"}]}], ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", 
  "1"}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 3.812814624563648*^9}, {
  3.8128158343188505`*^9, 3.812815836863346*^9}, {3.8128159122615914`*^9, 
  3.81281591412246*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"972c024b-4106-49a0-b4ea-\
afda912df8df"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "As our electrons are no longer constrained to be in the same ",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " orbital, they don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t necessarily have opposite spins, \
which means we have a range of possible values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 3.8128146034871693`*^9}, {
   3.8128148840894175`*^9, 3.8128148974362593`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "40359b97-bda9-41fb-bbcc-3548e51754b2"],
 " from 1 to \[Minus]1. Similarly, the different ",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " orbitals have different values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["l",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 3.812814624563648*^9}, {
   3.8128158343188505`*^9, 3.812815836863346*^9}, {3.8128159122615914`*^9, 
   3.81281591412246*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "3c399ecb-87e7-4fb4-9709-6de36ac0f497"],
 ", so we can have a range of values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["L",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 3.8128146034871693`*^9}, {
   3.8128148840894175`*^9, 3.8128148974362593`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "45123987-dff6-4e70-947b-3bfc60421cc0"],
 " from \[Minus]2 to 2. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812815845428276*^9, 3.812815985054877*^9}, {
  3.812905048833805*^9, 3.8129050519070415`*^9}, {3.8129050855318356`*^9, 
  3.8129050883760443`*^9}, {3.918404660146883*^9, 
  3.9184046621062937`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dbae0146-3bf6-4fb1-a1e2-\
977bee8084fa"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To find how many electron configurations correspond to each possible set of \
values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 3.8128146034871693`*^9}, {
   3.8128148840894175`*^9, 3.8128148974362593`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "705b45ba-d947-47ce-a2d5-f9fd9b359b3e"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["L",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 3.8128146034871693`*^9}, {
   3.8128148840894175`*^9, 3.8128148974362593`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "26760cfb-3b2a-4228-8c59-3e7053cdb641"],
 ", it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s useful to construct a table. Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \
have the values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["L",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 3.8128146034871693`*^9}, {
   3.8128148840894175`*^9, 3.8128148974362593`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "c1f53b61-8748-4314-8bbe-f1663b1bc2a3"],
 " as rows and the values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.812814561465426*^9, 3.8128146034871693`*^9}, {
   3.8128148840894175`*^9, 3.8128148974362593`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "c7864ba1-a25e-4c5d-b6cd-d51c306f7181"],
 " as columns and fill the table with the possible electron configurations,"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.8128157872778006`*^9, {3.8128159893962507`*^9, 
   3.812816112790848*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"98b2226e-db74-4b50-915c-\
184da2b63e61"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[GridBox[{
   {Cell[" ",ExpressionUUID->"8b951e1a-434c-449d-a4df-edc64574b897"], " ", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], " "},
   {
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["L",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "0", "1"},
   {
    RowBox[{"-", "2"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", 
       SuperscriptBox["1", "+"]}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"-", 
       SuperscriptBox["1", "\[Minus]"]}]}], ")"}], " "},
   {
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", 
       SuperscriptBox["1", "-"]}], ",", 
      SuperscriptBox["0", "-"]}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"-", 
        SuperscriptBox["1", "+"]}], ",", 
       SuperscriptBox["0", "-"]}], ")"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"-", 
        SuperscriptBox["1", "-"]}], ",", 
       SuperscriptBox["0", "+"]}], ")"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", 
       SuperscriptBox["1", "+"]}], ",", 
      SuperscriptBox["0", "+"]}], ")"}]},
   {"0", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", 
       SuperscriptBox["1", "-"]}], ",", 
      SuperscriptBox["1", "-"]}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["1", "+"], ",", 
       RowBox[{"-", 
        SuperscriptBox["1", "-"]}]}], ")"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["1", "-"], ",", 
       RowBox[{"-", 
        SuperscriptBox["1", "+"]}]}], ")"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["0", "+"], ",", 
       SuperscriptBox["0", "-"]}], ")"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", 
       SuperscriptBox["1", "+"]}], ",", 
      SuperscriptBox["1", "+"]}], ")"}]},
   {"1", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["1", "-"], ",", 
      SuperscriptBox["0", "-"]}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["1", "+"], ",", 
       SuperscriptBox["0", "-"]}], ")"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["1", "-"], ",", 
       SuperscriptBox["0", "+"]}], ")"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["1", "+"], ",", 
      SuperscriptBox["0", "+"]}], ")"}]},
   {"2", " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["1", "+"], ",", 
      SuperscriptBox["1", "\[Minus]"]}], ")"}], " "}
  },
  GridBoxDividers->{
   "Columns" -> {{True}}, 
    "Rows" -> {{
      True}}}]],ExpressionUUID->"e1800832-9dd3-4e0f-8470-e9c44fb1a377"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812816183242498*^9, 3.812816428079652*^9}, {
  3.812816462800923*^9, 3.8128166290840225`*^9}, {3.81281717239036*^9, 
  3.812817174537908*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b424be31-0af5-431f-9354-\
703f6464b9b3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where we are using the base of each configuration to indicate the value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "l"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ad484fc4-36e1-4f17-b8a7-321c7963e2ed"],
 " (\[Minus]1, 0, or 1) and the superscript to indicate the value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "s"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "99acc81d-ca77-47c1-aa8a-84ceccbb3962"],
 " (+ for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"+", 
    FractionBox["1", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dd1140c5-5d98-4849-a6dc-87347d52a4ba"],
 " and \[Minus] for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Minus]", 
    FractionBox["1", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8b1d584d-1fd7-4fcf-8106-50dbec7c6185"],
 "). Note that we don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t double-count equivalent electron \
configurations (e.g., ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"(", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", 
     SuperscriptBox["1", "+"]}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"-", 
     SuperscriptBox["1", "\[Minus]"]}]}], ")"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ad595237-be9f-4280-bdd5-022b326b986c"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"(", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", 
     SuperscriptBox["1", "\[Minus]"]}], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"-", 
     SuperscriptBox["1", "+"]}]}], ")"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e1ff84b0-fa88-4c69-b813-9e70318433ce"],
 " because they are indistinguishable. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128131455790114`*^9, 3.8128131586854167`*^9}, 
   3.8128132115138025`*^9, {3.812816643985859*^9, 3.812816726005498*^9}, {
   3.812816785695631*^9, 3.8128167908258915`*^9}, {3.8128169123523693`*^9, 
   3.812816949932029*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2c9abd21-2dd3-4d9d-94eb-\
7bba322011f2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Remember that we are really after the values of ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " to define our term symbol. Earlier, we defined a relationship between ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["M", "L"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "88dd65a1-0b40-4ded-96cf-d50f9705416b"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["M", "S"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6dda7615-f8c5-4d6f-99da-191970d9a1d0"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", which we can now use. First, we know that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["M", "L"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dbe46639-b16f-4b61-9328-c47dbe695939"],
 " ranges from \[Minus]2 to 2, there must be some state with ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = 2. Because we can only obtain the values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["M", "L"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", "2"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "79c8d08f-7d83-4941-ba62-b579db9a1cca"],
 " with a value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["M", "S"], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c4c4e4b0-4796-47c8-8a92-cb4888b48d67"],
 ", there must be a set of states with ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = 2 and ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = 0. There will be five of these states (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["M", "L"], "=", 
     RowBox[{"-", "2"}]}], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"2", " ", "and", " ", 
      SubscriptBox["M", "S"]}], "=", "0", " "}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"a78fcec5-8065-4cdc-ade8-cc56661a7580"],
 ") with term symbol"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128170209729996`*^9, 3.8128172281938133`*^9}, {
   3.8128172946142626`*^9, 3.812817393735076*^9}, {3.8128176090680017`*^9, 
   3.8128177627394495`*^9}, 3.812817826997938*^9, {3.9184047326270065`*^9, 
   3.9184047338308535`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d50a0188-60f4-47b0-96a7-\
ae806bbb5337"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox["", "1"], 
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["D",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128152039945197`*^9, 3.812815256576949*^9}, {
  3.8128178519973774`*^9, 
  3.8128178576384025`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3dce0beb-3676-4446-a1a4-\
900773f91b24"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where we have used the relationship between ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["M",
     FontWeight->"Plain",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["J",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontWeight->"Plain",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["L",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontWeight->"Plain",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
    3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
    3.8128123854295173`*^9}, {3.812812734843032*^9, 3.812812738001706*^9}, {
    3.812812777924115*^9, 3.812812784141674*^9}, {3.8128129529930706`*^9, 
    3.8128130907006335`*^9}, 3.812813186181301*^9, {3.812814998961049*^9, 
    3.8128149993964257`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "645763a0-9ff8-416c-b0d1-5fa779fe590f"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " in equation (12) to determine the value of ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812817864220606*^9, 3.8128179273169174`*^9}, {
  3.937054531577238*^9, 
  3.937054531924576*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"10978cb2-3c20-4f12-b3e5-\
32b76295b47a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Now, we still need to assign term symbols to the remaining possible \
configurations. We still have states with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["M", "L"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a66db431-86ab-4276-b805-6647538b7667"],
 " values of 1 and \[Minus]1 that are unaccounted for, which indicates a set \
of states with an ",
 StyleBox["L ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "value of 1. We see that for each of these states, we can have values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
    3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
    3.8128123854295173`*^9}, {3.812812734843032*^9, 3.812812738001706*^9}, {
    3.812812777924115*^9, 3.812812784141674*^9}, {3.8128129529930706`*^9, 
    3.8128130907006335`*^9}, 3.812813186181301*^9, {3.812814998961049*^9, 
    3.8128149993964257`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "91570499-b42f-41f1-b87c-07a2e042747e"],
 " of \[Minus]1, 0, or 1, which would arise from an ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " value of 1. Therefore, we should have states with the term symbol of the \
type"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128179411973658`*^9, 3.812817975407347*^9}, {
  3.812818038712723*^9, 
  3.8128181719130955`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"da0ae523-e391-4de4-95bf-\
d7e54290538a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox["", "3"], 
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["P",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["J",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128152039945197`*^9, 3.812815256576949*^9}, {
  3.8128178519973774`*^9, 3.8128178576384025`*^9}, {3.8128181778326225`*^9, 
  3.81281818689855*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d136604f-ebe7-4a36-a556-\
ba7ed147fd52"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To determine the possible values of ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", recall that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["M",
     FontWeight->"Plain",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["J",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontWeight->"Plain",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["L",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontWeight->"Plain",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
    3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
    3.8128123854295173`*^9}, {3.812812734843032*^9, 3.812812738001706*^9}, {
    3.812812777924115*^9, 3.812812784141674*^9}, {3.8128129529930706`*^9, 
    3.8128130907006335`*^9}, 3.812813186181301*^9, {3.812814998961049*^9, 
    3.8128149993964257`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "6e4da677-93ae-4480-8903-6ab28e5048ff"],
 ". Taking into account the three different possible values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
    3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
    3.8128123854295173`*^9}, {3.812812734843032*^9, 3.812812738001706*^9}, {
    3.812812777924115*^9, 3.812812784141674*^9}, {3.8128129529930706`*^9, 
    3.8128130907006335`*^9}, 3.812813186181301*^9, {3.812814998961049*^9, 
    3.8128149993964257`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "4f6a3508-c9cf-4d6f-9c5c-02120b95f164"],
 " and three different possible values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["M", "L"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ee53e07c-0ffe-4c68-80ea-44b0d9588499"],
 ", we can have ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["M",
    FontWeight->"Plain",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["J",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
    3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
    3.8128123854295173`*^9}, {3.812812734843032*^9, 3.812812738001706*^9}, {
    3.812812777924115*^9, 3.812812784141674*^9}, {3.8128129529930706`*^9, 
    3.8128130907006335`*^9}, 3.812813186181301*^9, {3.812814998961049*^9, 
    3.8128149993964257`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "72ed8a9a-29c4-4b20-89f4-7f270c755808"],
 " values of \[Minus]2, \[Minus]1, \[Minus]1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, and 2. If we \
write these values in the form (\[Minus]2, \[Minus]1, 0, 1, 2), (\[Minus]1, \
0, 1), and (0), we see that they correspond to ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " values of 2, 1, and 0. So our term symbols for these states are"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128181957689075`*^9, 3.812818205925433*^9}, {
  3.8128183101613636`*^9, 3.812818355447464*^9}, {3.812818428394126*^9, 
  3.812818591014988*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"33646b43-68e7-408b-9aa0-\
d1b47671fa4e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["", "3"], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]}], ",", 
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["", "3"], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"]}], ",", " ", 
  RowBox[{"and", "  ", 
   SuperscriptBox["", "3"], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "0"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128152039945197`*^9, 3.812815256576949*^9}, {
  3.8128178519973774`*^9, 3.8128178576384025`*^9}, {3.8128181778326225`*^9, 
  3.81281818689855*^9}, {3.812818596826277*^9, 
  3.812818617282662*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"90e8d100-5cc8-494e-b2ea-\
0dc6e7014d38"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We still have an additional state with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontWeight->"Plain",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["L",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", "0"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["M",
      FontWeight->"Plain",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["S",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", "0"}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128117549390078`*^9, 3.812811805160163*^9}, {
    3.8128122054106054`*^9, 3.812812225217738*^9}, {3.8128123371306987`*^9, 
    3.8128123854295173`*^9}, {3.812812734843032*^9, 3.812812738001706*^9}, {
    3.812812777924115*^9, 3.812812784141674*^9}, {3.8128129529930706`*^9, 
    3.8128130907006335`*^9}, 3.812813186181301*^9, {3.812814998961049*^9, 
    3.8128149993964257`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "9112b2b2-b00d-4541-b3b4-ed8608af5701"],
 " that must correspond to a different term symbol. Since this state stands \
alone, it must arise from a state with ",
 StyleBox["L",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = 0, and ",
 StyleBox["S",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = 0, or a term symbol of"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128186622658887`*^9, 
  3.8128187415179224`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"67b27f84-2b08-4e17-ab99-\
3cd589b7a867"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox["", "1"], 
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "0"]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128152039945197`*^9, 3.812815256576949*^9}, 
   3.8128187675924606`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"7c0e3493-82e8-46dc-be00-\
1cc6de6eca19"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "From these results, we observe that ",
 StyleBox["the values of ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["J",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" for a given value of ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["L",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" and ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["S ",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox["are given by ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812818862313166*^9, 3.8128189309949245`*^9}, {
  3.812819034899102*^9, 
  3.8128190372346077`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c3ff0dd5-dda8-4a44-93a6-\
3ee59df16fac"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["L",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "-", 
    StyleBox["S",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], ",", "...", ",", 
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["L",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "+", 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "-", "1"}], ",", 
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["L",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "+", 
   StyleBox["S",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128189398291893`*^9, 
  3.8128190295450015`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0f8f746e-6fe0-4370-9189-\
5933389acf3f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["A Note About Spin Multiplicity", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128191021921763`*^9, 
  3.8128191066925616`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7abc162c-0bcf-4083-8fd5-\
0171a746dd85"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s talk briefly about the value of spin multiplicity. \
We have seen that we often encounter either singlet states (e.g. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["", "1"], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["S",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "0"]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128152039945197`*^9, 3.812815256576949*^9}, 
    3.8128187675924606`*^9},ExpressionUUID->
  "c2087403-ed9c-4232-b1b6-84b2c994d547"],
 ") or triplet states (e.g. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["", "3"], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["S",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128152039945197`*^9, 3.812815256576949*^9}, 
    3.8128187675924606`*^9},ExpressionUUID->
  "1c59ce2b-fb4a-49f2-bdc6-6e7815f15d5e"],
 ") . We can have the association in our mind that triplet states indicate \
unpaired electron spins (e.g. ++ or \[Minus]\[Minus]), and singlet states \
indicate paired electron states (+\[Minus]). However, note that in reality it\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s a bit more complicated than that because our two states \
with different electron spins are actually a linear combination of spin \
states. We have two states that we normally write as +\[Minus],"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812819108818945*^9, 3.812819254687405*^9}, {
  3.8128192854949756`*^9, 3.812819385001923*^9}, {3.812819416034181*^9, 
  3.812819516040346*^9}, {3.812819853240506*^9, 3.812819950756485*^9}, {
  3.812820529061139*^9, 3.81282057205505*^9}, {3.9184048483649883`*^9, 
  3.9184048636136007`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8c08af91-349f-4907-b1a1-\
d872481b4ede"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "+"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]], "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", 
     RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}], "\[Beta]", 
     RowBox[{"(", "2", ")"}]}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"\[Beta]", 
     RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}], "\[Alpha]", 
     RowBox[{"(", "2", ")"}]}]}], "]"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810112811439228*^9, 3.8101128248442793`*^9}, {
   3.810479494926491*^9, 3.8104795038498344`*^9}, {3.810479572543576*^9, 
   3.8104796147383184`*^9}, {3.8104802055659895`*^9, 
   3.8104802433915305`*^9}, {3.8104802785189395`*^9, 
   3.8104802814214115`*^9}, {3.8109915300785556`*^9, 
   3.8109916793993816`*^9}, {3.810991710031681*^9, 3.8109918292023373`*^9}, {
   3.810994488524798*^9, 3.810994499853472*^9}, {3.8109948928195066`*^9, 
   3.8109948950763626`*^9}, {3.8109949491606197`*^9, 3.810995087249513*^9}, {
   3.8109951188614283`*^9, 3.8109951226144466`*^9}, {3.8115998145208507`*^9, 
   3.8115999093225703`*^9}, 3.8119468581508093`*^9, {3.8126173912859564`*^9, 
   3.8126174353481674`*^9}, {3.812617986792708*^9, 3.812617987701547*^9}, {
   3.8126194925193796`*^9, 3.812619503416272*^9}, {3.812619551056244*^9, 
   3.812619564308283*^9}, {3.812619992990877*^9, 3.8126200208718753`*^9}, 
   3.8126201248430705`*^9, {3.812620163920018*^9, 3.8126201669704065`*^9}, {
   3.8126204678526173`*^9, 3.8126204826728334`*^9}, {3.8126205155312433`*^9, 
   3.81262057853043*^9}, {3.812620660711446*^9, 3.812620661159943*^9}, {
   3.8126208302516937`*^9, 3.8126208466299543`*^9}, {3.812620980916898*^9, 
   3.8126209810859137`*^9}, 3.8126287856964226`*^9, {3.812629271581931*^9, 
   3.8126292755855017`*^9}, {3.8126293423208475`*^9, 3.812629351460653*^9}, {
   3.8126294501142464`*^9, 3.8126295143102984`*^9}, {3.812629684693431*^9, 
   3.812629684832785*^9}, {3.8128207562103453`*^9, 
   3.812820780041172*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"564e189a-68f3-499a-8ac1-\
aed5ff78b888"],

Cell["and", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8128207838395863`*^9, 
  3.81282078404889*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cd2eb173-168c-417c-a652-\
812fcc67f51c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "-"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]], "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", 
     RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}], "\[Beta]", 
     RowBox[{"(", "2", ")"}]}], "-", 
